issue.title: Github project languages (linguist) information not visible
issue.body: I have [github project] (https://github.com/thamsrang/jquery-hashchange). I have html, js files. But language statistics not showing. Can you kindly update me.

comment.body:
It looks like all the content in your repository is being treated as [vendored](https://github.com/github/linguist#ignore-vendored-files) or [generated](https://github.com/github/linguist#generated-file-detection) content.

If you clone the repository and run Linguist on it, you won't see any results, which explains why we're not showing any language statistics for the repository on GitHub:

```sh
› git clone https://github.com/thamsrang/jquery-hashchange.git ~/jquery-hashchange
› bundle exec linguist ~/jquery-hashchange --breakdown
```

You'll need to re-arrange the repository so that the contents aren't treated as vendored or generated if you want Linguist to generate language statistics.

Add and_criteria_met and or_criteria_met to the check result

Allows the use of nice logic in the handlebars template:

```
{{#if and_criteria_met}}success{{else}}danger{{/if}}
```

pull_request.title: Vendor Octicon styles
pull_request.body:
I dropped [Octicons](http://octicons.github.com/) into a project using the default [instructions](http://octicons.github.com/usage/), which resulted in Linguist deciding my project was mostly composed of CSS.

In the spirit of vendoring libraries like [Bootstrap](https://github.com/github/linguist/blob/50ab58e91f19260b11cf92b92c5b8e8c0d79f51c/lib/linguist/vendor.yml#L37) we might like to also vendor the Octicons CSS/SCSS files.

/cc @github/linguist @cameronmcefee
